{"sectionId":771,"sectionIdLiteral":"771","humanId":"lesson-347","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Anger must come from judgment. Judgment is  the weapon I would use against myself,  to keep the miracle away from me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 347"},"annotation":"W-347","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-347\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"771#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, I want what goes against my will, and do not want what is my will to have.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Straighten my mind, my Father.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>It is sick.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>But You have offered freedom, and I choose to claim Your gift today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>And so I give all judgment to the One You gave to me to judge for me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>He sees what I behold, and yet He knows the truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>He looks on pain, and yet He understands it is not real, and in His understanding it is healed.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>He gives the miracles my dreams would hide from my awareness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>Let Him judge today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:10\"><span class=\"snr\">10</span>I do not know my will, but He is sure it is Your Own.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#1:11\"><span class=\"snr\">11</span>And He will speak for me, and call Your miracles to come to me.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"771#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Listen today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"771#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Be very still, and hear the gentle Voice for God assuring you that He has judged you as the Son He loves.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Father, I want what goes against my will, and do not want what is my will to have. Straighten my mind, my Father. It is sick. But You have offered freedom, and I choose to claim Your gift today. And","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 347: Anger must come from judgment.‚Ä¶ | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†347 ‚ÄúAnger must come from judgment. Judgment is the weapon I would use against myself, to keep the miracle away from me‚Äù: ‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"13. What Is a Miracle?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":764,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-a-miracle"]}},{"label":"Lesson 347","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":771,"slugs":["lesson-347","anger-must-come-from-judgment-judgment-is-the"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"13. What Is a Miracle?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":764,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-a-miracle"]}},{"label":"Lesson 347","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":771,"slugs":["lesson-347","anger-must-come-from-judgment-judgment-is-the"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId"